  "_meta": {
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "purpose": "Canonical MCP response shape -- single source of truth for both /mcp web and context-repo-mcp npm",
    "generatedAt": "2026-04-30",
    "toolCount": 28,
    "exempt": ["search", "fetch"],
    "notes": [
      "All `text` strings are lifted verbatim from app/[transport]/route.ts. Action tools follow the web 'Successfully X' pattern (npm '\u2713 X' wording is migrated in Phase 3).",
      "structuredContent mirrors the full REST response body. List endpoints retain the {data, pagination} envelope; single-resource reads keep the {data} envelope; action tools return the REST response body verbatim.",
      "Delete tools synthesize {id, deleted: true} for structuredContent because REST returns 204/null. The same shape is used for the idempotent-404 (no-op) branch -- the difference is only in the `text` wording.",
      "get_collection emits two fixtures: the default (includeItems omitted, treated as true per M-050) which performs a second REST call to /items, and the includeItems:false branch which performs a single REST call.",
      "deep_expand emits two fixtures: a normal-results entry and the M-033 self-healing empty-results entry whose text matches route.ts:1432 verbatim.",
      "search and fetch are EXEMPT from Markdown per the OpenAI Apps SDK Company-Knowledge contract -- their `text` field stays JSON-as-text. They DO get a structuredContent mirror of the same JSON for uniformity (per locked decision Q5 in the audit).",
      "Non-ASCII characters are emitted via \\u escape sequences so the file is pure ASCII-safe at the source; downstream JSON parsers materialize them as their natural Unicode glyphs (em-dash \\u2014, folder emoji \\ud83d\\udcc1).",
      "Mock REST IDs are deterministic and timestamp-free: prompt_aaa, prompt_bbb, doc_bbb, doc_eee, col_ccc, chunk_ddd, etc. The fetch fixture intentionally uses raw convex IDs (aaa/bbb/ccc) in its REST mock so the encodeMcpId() prefix yields prompt_aaa / document_bbb / collection_ccc in the output payload."
    ]
  },
